      "content": "It sounds like you might be experiencing a migraine, which can indeed feel like a bolt of lightning. A good start would be to drink some water and take an ibuprofen, but if the headache persists or worsens, consider taking a Tylenol and maybe a small dose of caffeine. If you feel nauseous, ginger tea could help. If the symptoms don't improve, you might want to try a combination of caffeine and aspirin, but be cautious with the dosage. Remember, if you ever feel dizzy or have trouble standing, it's a good idea to lie down and rest. But if you feel like you're just having a minor headache, these remedies should help you feel better. Just make sure to take it easy for a while.",
