      "content": "A migraine can indeed strike suddenly and intensely, even if it's just for a brief moment. It's not uncommon for them to occur without warning. As for aspirin and caffeine, it's best to take them separately. Start with the aspirin, 325 mg, and then wait about 30 minutes before taking the caffeine, around 100 mg. This will help prevent any potential stomach upset. If you don't feel any relief after taking these, you might want to try a combination of Tylenol and caffeine, 500 mg of Tylenol and 100 mg of caffeine, but only if you're not allergic to Tylenol. Remember, if your symptoms don't improve or if you experience any severe side effects, it's important to seek medical attention. But for now, these remedies should help you feel better. Just make sure to listen to your body and take it easy for a while.",
